WEBVTT

00:00:00.640 --> 00:00:05.040
Let's show you how to deploy your data science content to Posit Connect Cloud.

00:00:05.040 --> 00:00:08.640
In this example, we'll be deploying a Shiny for Python application,

00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:11.440
but Posit Connect Cloud is not limited to just this framework.

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:17.600
Deploying on Connect Cloud starts with the GitHub repository.

00:00:19.120 --> 00:00:22.000
Here, we'll create an empty repository named dashboard,

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:25.840
and then clone it down to our computer.

00:00:30.879 --> 00:00:33.279
Next, we'll create our Shiny for Python application.

00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:37.439
Here, we'll use an existing Shiny for Python template

00:00:37.439 --> 00:00:39.360
and save it into our cloned repository.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.959
We'll follow the instructions to install the template dependencies

00:00:50.959 --> 00:00:52.160
and run it in Positron.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:12.080
Let's run this application locally first.

00:01:15.760 --> 00:01:20.879
We'll open the app.py file and click the play button from the Shiny VS Code extension.

00:01:30.559 --> 00:01:36.080
We can see the reactivity of the application when we change the checkboxes.

00:01:37.680 --> 00:01:50.080
Next, we need to get all the code to our GitHub repository.

00:01:50.559 --> 00:01:54.160
Now that the code is on GitHub, let's go to Connect Cloud and deploy our application.

00:01:56.160 --> 00:01:59.760
After you log in and connect your GitHub account to Connect Cloud,

00:01:59.760 --> 00:02:06.160
we can click publish, Shiny, and select our repository.

00:02:10.080 --> 00:02:12.160
Our current application is on the main page,

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:14.559
and we can see that we have a lot of code that we need to deploy.

00:02:15.520 --> 00:02:24.639
Our current application is on the main branch and is named app.py.

00:02:26.639 --> 00:02:38.639
We then hit publish.

00:02:45.119 --> 00:02:54.639
Our app is now published at the URL.

00:02:56.720 --> 00:03:08.639
Now, let's make a change to the capitalization of the dashboard title.

00:03:15.440 --> 00:03:20.639
The changes will automatically republish the application.

00:03:22.639 --> 00:03:26.639
You do not need to click the republish button by default.

00:03:30.639 --> 00:03:34.639
In the content settings, by clicking on it here,

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:36.720
you have the option to turn off auto-republish

00:03:36.720 --> 00:03:40.720
and also the option to give your content a custom URL.

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:46.720
Posit Connect Cloud is an easy way to deploy straight from an existing GitHub repository

00:03:46.720 --> 00:03:52.720
and share your data science work.

00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:56.800
Posit Connect Cloud is an easy way to deploy straight from an existing GitHub repository

00:03:56.800 --> 00:04:00.800
and share your data science work.

